Program: Discovery
Title: Water Works - the Mississippi River
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrydh
Last Broadcast Date: 13 May 2003
An exploration into the complex and enormous structures used in flood control in the US. In the southern United States flood-prone regions have long lived with a struggle with the Mississippi river. The programme looks at the attempts to prevent the river from changing its course. Presenter: Julian Siddle. Show less